Use aim, kleem and sauH as beeja, shakti and keelaka. Repeat the same 3 beejas for anga and kara nyaasas.
 
For dhyaana, you can pick any verse of Saraswati. For example, here is one small verse written by Kaalidaasa:
 
shaaradaa shaaradaambhoja vadanaa vadanaambuje
sarvadaa sarvadaasmaakam sannidhiH sannidhiH kriyaat
 
Each word is repeated twice with two different meanings above. Kaalidaasa is a gifted poet. He was an illiterate ignoramus who turned into a great scholar when the Mother appeared and blessed. There is something outworldly in his poetic expressions.
 
Another popular dhyaana shloka for Saraswati is:
 
sarasvati namastubhyam varade kaamarUpiNi
vidyaaraMbhaM kariShyaami siddhirbhavatu me sadaa
 
There are many more. Pick the one you like.
 
After panchopachara pooja, do pradhaana homam with any Saraswati mantra you like. I will give some options below. I am using iTrans notation below. You can cut & paste it in ITranslator software to see mantras in Sanskrit with Vedic intonation marked. First mantra is a simple naama mantra with beeja added. Second mantra is a Gayatri mantra from Rigveda. Third one has beejas added.
 
